
[1]scrupulously

   SCRU'PULOUSLY, adv. With a nice regard to minute particulars or to
   exact propriety.

   The duty consists not scrupolously in minutes and half hours. Taylor.

   Henry was scrupulously careful not to ascribe the sucess to himself.
   Addison.
